<p id="p0085" class="p">Hence, to go from percentage to daily mortality, it suffices to take into account the mean mortality in Antwerp during hot days, meaning days with mortality attributable to heat, as follows:
 <disp-formula id="fo0015" class="disp-formula">
  <math id="M3" display="block" altimg="si3.gif" overflow="scroll" class="math">
   <mtext class="mtext">mortality attributable to heat</mtext>
   <mo class="mo">=</mo>
   <mfrac class="mfrac">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo class="mo">%</mo>
     <mtext class="mtext">mortality attributable to heat</mtext>
     <mo class="mo">Â·</mo>
     <mtext class="mtext">mean mortality</mtext>
    </mrow>
    <mn class="mn">100</mn>
   </mfrac>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
 <disp-formula id="fo0020" class="disp-formula">
  <math id="M4" display="block" altimg="si4.gif" overflow="scroll" class="math">
   <mtext class="mtext">daily mortality attributable to heat</mtext>
   <mo class="mo">=</mo>
   <mfrac class="mfrac">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mtext class="mtext">mortality attributable to heat</mtext>
     <mspace width="0.25em" class="mspace"/>
    </mrow>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mtext class="mtext">number of hot days</mtext>
    </mrow>
   </mfrac>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
